          "id": 2,
          "title": "Part 2: Riverside Leisure Centre Tour",
          "description": "A staff member gives new visitors a tour of a newly renovated community leisure centre.",
          "audio": "audio/ViaTestPrep_Unique_1_Part2.mp3",
          "diagram": "<img src=\"images/listening_unique1_p2_plan.png\" alt=\"Riverside Leisure Centre ground floor plan\" style=\"max-width:520px;\" />",
          "transcript": "<p><b>GUIDE:</b> Good evening, everyone, and welcome to this evening's tour of the newly renovated Riverside Leisure Centre. My name's Alice, and I'm the centre's activities coordinator. I know a lot of you have been looking forward to this reopening, so thank you for your patience during the building work.</p><p><b>GUIDE:</b> The renovation actually took a little longer than we originally planned. We'd hoped to reopen in the spring, but a delay in the delivery of specialist flooring for the main sports hall pushed everything back by several months. It wasn't the electrics or the plumbing that caused the holdup, as some of you may have heard, it really did just come down to that flooring.</p><p><b>GUIDE:</b> Now, one of our main goals with this renovation was to make the centre more accessible to everyone in the community. We've always had strong classes for older adults, but our real focus going forward is on expanding provision for teenagers, who previously had very little dedicated to them here. We've brought in two new youth sports coaches, and we'll be running free after-school sessions three times a week.</p><p><b>GUIDE:</b> Before we start the tour properly, there is one important new rule I need to mention. Because of the specialist sprung flooring we've just installed in the main sports hall, everyone must change into clean indoor trainers before entering that hall. We've installed lockers just outside for your outdoor shoes.</p><p><b>GUIDE:</b> Right, let's look at the map in your welcome pack. We're currently standing at the Main Entrance, at the bottom of the map. Immediately on your left as you come in is the Reception Desk, where you can sort out membership renewals. If you walk straight down the central corridor, the first door on your right leads into the newly refurbished Swimming Pool, which now has a hoist for easier accessibility.</p><p><b>GUIDE:</b> Continuing down that same corridor, just past the pool, you'll find a small, quiet room, that's our new Relaxation Room, intended as a calm space away from the noise of the main centre. At the very end of the central corridor, the corridor opens out into the large Sports Hall I mentioned earlier.</p><p><b>GUIDE:</b> Now, if we go back to the Main Entrance and instead take the corridor on the right, past Reception, the large room in the top right corner of the building is our brand-new Fitness Gym, which has excellent natural light from the windows overlooking the river. Finally, halfway along that right-hand corridor, directly opposite the gym entrance, you'll find the Riverside Cafe, a nice spot for a coffee after your workout. Every penny of profit from the cafe goes straight back into funding our free youth programmes, rather than to an outside company.</p><p><b>GUIDE:</b> Right, before we head off on the tour itself, does anyone have any questions?</p>",
